# CA Lab Works – VHDL Digital Design

## 📌 Introduction
This repository contains basic Digital Logic Design experiments implemented using VHDL (VHSIC Hardware Description Language). The designs are simulated using the open-source tool GHDL and waveform analysis is done using GTKWave.

---

## 🎯 Objective
To design, implement, and simulate basic digital logic gates using VHDL and verify their functionality using open-source simulation tools.

---

## 🛠️ Tools Used
- VHDL (Hardware Description Language)
- GHDL (Compiler & Simulator)
- GTKWave (Waveform Viewer)
- Visual Studio Code

---

## 🔧 Implemented Circuits
- AND Gate
- OR Gate
- NOT Gate
- NAND Gate
- NOR Gate
- XOR Gate
- XNOR Gate

Each circuit includes:
- VHDL design file
- Testbench file
- Simulation output (waveform)

---

## ⚙️ Simulation Flow
1. Write VHDL design code
2. Write testbench
3. Compile using GHDL
4. Run simulation
5. View waveform using GTKWave

Example commands:
```bash
ghdl -a design.vhdl
ghdl -a testbench.vhdl
ghdl -e testbench
ghdl -r testbench --vcd=wave.vcd
gtkwave wave.vcd
